import string, random

class Codec:
    def __init__(self):
        self.alphabet = string.ascii_letters + string.digits
        self.url2code = {}
        self.code2url = {}
        self.base = "http://tinyurl.com/"

    def encode(self, longUrl: str) -> str:
        if longUrl in self.url2code:
            return self.base + self.url2code[longUrl]
        code = ''.join(random.choice(self.alphabet) for _ in range(6))
        while code in self.code2url:
            code = ''.join(random.choice(self.alphabet) for _ in range(6))
        self.url2code[longUrl] = code
        self.code2url[code] = longUrl
        return self.base + code

    def decode(self, shortUrl: str) -> str:
        return self.code2url[shortUrl[-6:]]
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) expected for both encode and decode
space complexity: O(N) where N is the number of URLs stored
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses two hash maps for O(1) bidirectional lookup; generates a random 6-character code (62^6 ≈ 57B possibilities) to keep collision probability negligible. Constant-time operations dominate, making it energy-efficient.

